%T A397657 0,0,0,120,5,160,540,480,0,200,600,360,0,0,300,240,0,0,0,120,0,0,0,0,
%U A397657 0,0,0,0,0,720,6,480,3240,5760,3600,0,1170,6000,7560,2880,0,0,3360,5040,2160,0,0,0,2520,1440,0,0,0,0,720,0,0,0,0,0
%N A397657 Triangle of triangles T(n,t,c) read by rows: number of functions f:{1..n}->{1..n} whose functional graph has maximal tail length (rho-height) exactly t and exactly c cyclic (periodic) points; n >= 1, 0 <= t <= n-1, 1 <= c <= n.
%C A397657 A functional graph decomposes into directed cycles, with a rooted tree attached at each cyclic point. Its maximal tail length is at most t exactly when every attached tree has height at most t. Let e_t(x) be the e.g.f. for rooted labeled trees of height at most t, with e_{-1}=0, e_0=x, and e_t=x*exp(e_{t-1}) for t>=1. Taking the difference between height bounds t and t-1 gives the formula below.
%C A397657 Row sums over t and c give n^n (A000312).
%C A397657 Summing over c gives A216242 (functions by height, i.e. maximal tail length).
%C A397657 Summing over t gives A066324 (functions by number of cyclic points); closed form C(n,c)*c!*c*n^(n-c-1) for c < n, and n! for c = n.
%C A397657 The t=1 slice (c < n) is A199673, T(n,c) = C(n,c)*c!*c^(n-c).
%C A397657 T(n,0,c) = n! if c = n, else 0 (the permutations). T(n,n-1,1) = n! (functional graphs that are a single path of n vertices ending in a fixed point).
%D A397657 P. Flajolet and A. Odlyzko, Random Mapping Statistics, in: Advances in Cryptology - EUROCRYPT '89, LNCS 434, Springer, 1990, pp. 329-354.
%D A397657 P. Flajolet and R. Sedgewick, Analytic Combinatorics, Cambridge University Press, 2009, Sections II.4 and III.7.
%F A397657 T(n,t,c) = n! * [x^n u^c] (1/(1 - u*e_t(x)) - 1/(1 - u*e_{t-1}(x))), where e_{-1}=0, e_0=x, and e_t=x*exp(e_{t-1}) for t>=1. The coefficients of e_t form A236396: A236396(n,t) = n! * [x^n] e_t(x).
%e A397657 Triangle blocks (n; rows t = 0..n-1; columns c = 1..n):
%e A397657   n=1: 1
%e A397657   n=2: [0,2; 2,0]
%e A397657   n=3: [0,0,6; 3,12,0; 6,0,0]
%e A397657   n=4: [0,0,0,24; 4,48,72,0; 36,48,0,0; 24,0,0,0]
%Y A397657 Cf. A236396 (coefficients of e_t), A216242 (row sums over c), A066324 (row sums over t), A199673 (t=1 slice), A000312 (n^n), A000142 (n!), A060281, A130534.
%K A397657 nonn,tabf,new
%O A397657 1,3
%A A397657 _Alex Towell_
